{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1c0b35e3-1eff-4271-833b-fde84da8036c","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed before it.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_jOti9Qi7eoqq7D5e2yORtO","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-4b94e9c23c084cc29ce856e0b1cb032d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-4b94e9c23c084cc29ce856e0b1cb032d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"1933ab4f-f1ae-4bc2-b559-0269b749f01a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear before them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the .fsproj:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. And `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should come last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n\n\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":453,"requestId":"F036:D4E0A:44A96B7:4C54294:69F9B07C"},"id":"dda96b29-c4d7-4119-82ad-751f27b67697","timestamp":"2026-05-05T08:55:32.608Z","parentId":"7469ab91-1a35-4ed5-9c3e-eb1155ca0811"}
